load ../infoflow-confidentiality.maude

--- Coverage: bank data flowing into a public-cleared egress sink is a leak. Bank
--- secrecy is not leq pub. The classic over-clearance exfiltration.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  secretSource(b1, bank) flow(b1, b2) egressSink(b2, pub)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Coverage: INCOMPARABLE compartments. Bank data flowing into a sink cleared
--- only for email is a leak, because bank is not leq email. This is the
--- multi-tenant separation property a two-point lattice cannot express.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  secretSource(b1, bank) flow(b1, b2) egressSink(b2, email)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Coverage: JOIN through an agent join box. The agent a1 mixes a bank input b1
--- and an email input b2; its output b3 carries both, so it exceeds a sink
--- cleared only for bank. Mixing two compartments outranks either alone.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  secretSource(b1, bank) secretSource(b2, email)
  flow(b1, a1) flow(b2, a1) flow(a1, b3) egressSink(b3, bank)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Coverage: declassifying one derivation does not make the source safe for its
--- OTHER uses. b1 is declassified to pub into b2, but b1 also flows raw into b3
--- which feeds a public egress sink. The raw second path still leaks.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  secretSource(b1, bank) declassify(b1, b2, pub) flow(b1, b3) egressSink(b3, pub)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Bite: data reaching a sink cleared at or above its level is never a leak. Bank
--- data to your own briefing cleared both, which dominates bank. No solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  secretSource(b1, bank) flow(b1, b2) egressSink(b2, both)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: the core property. Bank data reaching a public egress THROUGH a
--- declassify to pub is safe; the bounded typed value carries only pub.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  secretSource(b1, bank) declassify(b1, b2, pub) egressSink(b2, pub)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: a compartment may reach a sink cleared for exactly that compartment.
--- Bank data to a bank-cleared external bank portal is safe; bank leq bank.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  secretSource(b1, bank) flow(b1, b2) egressSink(b2, bank)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: a public-only program is never flagged. A pub-level source to a public
--- egress sink, no secret anywhere above pub.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  secretSource(b1, pub) flow(b1, b2) egressSink(b2, pub)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .
